These meetings are typically scheduled twice per year, with the first one being held before the start of the census and the second one taking place after the completion of the survey. During these meetings, participants discuss:

- Current statistical initiatives and progress;
- Challenges faced in implementing and maintaining statistical systems;
- Opportunities for improvement in the current system;
- Suggestions for future research and data collection needs;
- Recommendations for enhancing data usability and accessibility;
